{{Infobox protected area | name = Björnlandet National Park | alt_name = Björnlandets nationalpark | iucn_category = II | photo = Björnlandets nationalpark.jpg | photo_width = 288 | photo_caption = | location = [[Västerbotten County]], [[Sweden]] | nearest_city = [[Åsele]], [[Umeå]] | coords = {{coord|63|58|N|18|01|E|region:SE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | area_km2 = 11 | area_ref = <ref name="naturvårdsverket">{{cite web | title=Björnlandet National Park | url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Menu/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Bjornlandet-National-Park/ | publisher=[[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]] | accessdate=2009-02-26 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090404120111/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Menu/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Bjornlandet-National-Park/ | archivedate=2009-04-04 | df= }}</ref> | established = 1991<ref name="naturvårdsverket" /> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Environmental Protection Agency (Sweden)|Naturvårdsverket]] | website = }} '''Björnlandet''' is a [[national park]] in [[Västerbotten County]], northern [[Sweden]]. It was established in 1991 and covers an area of {{convert|11|km2|mi2|abbr=on}}.
Geographically it lies in southernmost [[Lapland (Sweden)|Lappland]], about {{convert|30|km|mi|abbr=on}} southwest of the hamlet ([[tätort|locality]]) of [[Fredrika, Sweden|Fredrika]], in [[Åsele Municipality]].
The park is notable for its large primeval forest and a geography that is distinguished by steep ravines and precipices. The fauna is comparatively of lower interest, due to the harsh climate and environment. {{Swedish National Parks|float=none}}
