{{Infobox protected area | name = 치악산국립공원, 雉岳山國立公園 | alt_name = Chiaksan National Park | iucn_category = II | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | location = [[Gangwon-do (South Korea)|Gangwon-do]], [[South Korea]] | nearest_city = Wonju | coordinates = {{coords|37.330|128.047|region:KR-42|notes=<ref>[http://protectedplanet.net/sites/Chiaksan_National_Park Chiaksan National Park] protectedplanet.net</ref>|display=inline, title}} | area = {{convert|181.57|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref name="knps.or.kr">{{cite web |url=http://english.knps.or.kr/Knp/Chiaksan/Intro/Introduction.aspx?MenuNum=1&Submenu=Npp |title=Chiaksan: Intro |author= |date= |website= |publisher=Korea National Park Service |accessdate=18 September 2010}}</ref> | established = 31 December 1984 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = Korea National Park Service | world_heritage_site = | url = }} {{South Korea national parks}} {{see also|Chiaksan}} '''Chiaksan National Park''' ({{lang-ko|'''치악산국립공원''', '''雉岳山國立公園'''}}) is located in the province of [[Gangwon-do (South Korea)|Gangwon-do]], [[South Korea]]. It was designated as the 16th national park in 1984.<ref name="knps.or.kr" /> The park is named after the {{convert|1288|m|ft|adj=on}}<ref>{{cite book| last=An Gyeong-ho | year=2003| title=신 한국 100 명산 ('The New' 100 Korean Mountains) |location=Seoul| publisher=깊은솔 (Gipeunsol)|isbn=978-89-89917-07-6|page=427}}</ref> mountain [[Chiaksan]], which in turn had its name changed from Jeokakasan to Chiaksan, meaning "Pheasant Peak Mountain", based on a myth about a man who saved a [[pheasant]] from being eaten by a snake.<ref>{{cite book |title=Frommer's South Korea |last=Hae-Jin Lee |first=Cecilia |year=2010 |publisher=[[Frommer's]] |isbn=978-0-470-59154-3 |page=382 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=95HEb92jABoC&pg=PA382 }}</ref> The park is home to a total of 821 plant species and 2,364 animal species. Among the animals 34 are endangered, including the [[Flying squirrel]] and [[Hodgson's Bat]].<ref name="knps.or.kr" />
