{{short description|Seamounts in Antarctica, named for Lieutenant Adrien Victor Joseph de Gerlache}}
'''De Gerlache Seamounts''' ({{Coord|65|0|S|90|30|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) are seamounts in [[Antarctica]], named for Lieutenant [[Adrien Victor Joseph de Gerlache]] ([[Royal Belgian Navy]]), Commander of the [[RV Belgica (1884)|''Belgica'']] during the first [[Belgian Antarctic Expedition]], 1896–1899.

