'''Imagbon''' is a town located in [[Ogun State]], Nigeria.<ref name="Vanguard News 2017"/><ref name="Times 2015"/> It is located to the western frontiers of [[Ijebu-Ode]], on a river tributary to the [[Lagos Lagoon]].
==Imagbon War== It is the site of the definitive [[Imagbon War]], also referred to as the Anglo-ljebu War,<ref name="West African Journal of Archaeology 2007"/> that occurred in 1892 between [[Yoruba people|Yoruba]] forces and the Imperial [[British military]].<ref name="Aladeojebi 2016 p. 494"/><ref name="Olabisi Onabanjo University"/><ref name="Onibere Adogbo 2010 p. 80"/> The military were assisted by protectorate treaty imposed on [[Lagos]] that enabled them to raise funds and troops supported by imported guns. A war memorial exists that commemorates the Imagbon War.<ref name="West African Journal of Archaeology 2007"/><ref>[https://oldnaija.wordpress.com/2015/11/04/the-british-ijebu-war-of-1892-the-battle-of-imagbon/ The British-Ijebu war of 1892 (The battle of Imagbon)]</ref>
