A '''sacerdotal state''' is a state whose [[Head of state|head]] is also an ecclesiastical leader designated by a religious body.  An example of this kind of state is the [[Vatican City]], whose head of state is the [[Pope]] of the [[Catholic Church]].<ref>[http://www.seechange.org/what's%20new/Dutch%20MPs.htm Dutch MPs protest Vatican international voting rights over AIDS<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[Andorra]] operates under a semi-sacerdotal system, as one of its co-heads of state is the [[Bishop of Urgell]]. In the past it was common for [[bishop]]s to assume civil as well as clerical power and rule as [[Prince-Bishop]]s.

